Light sails don't get much acceleration if the total mass of the craft is non-trivial. We're talking about a few kilograms of mass with a few square kilometers of sail that's one atom thick. Maybe some kind of automated space probe would be semi-suitable for this, but not something with people inside it. I would go for handwave-powered FTL, because all the semi-realistic hard-SF alternatives require our hero and a hundred generations of his descendants to die of old age before they get to the next planet. And if we can handwave something that can boost his ship up to 99% of c without killing him in the process, then slow the ship down again at its destination, then when he comes home it's still several thousand years later, his friends and family are all long dead and forgotten, the society that sent him out is unrecognizable if it even still exists, even the languages are all completely different. Unless that's the mood you're going for, better to handwave muh press-the-button-and-go FTL.
